          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "CYCTM"
                ],
                "institute": "1USAMSU"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Experiment performed at the Coupled",
                "Cyclotron Facility at the National Superconducting",
                "Cyclotron Laboratory (NSCL) at Michigan State",
                "University."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MAGSP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Reaction products were momentum analyzed with",
                "S800 spectrograph and identified using set of",
                "detectors in focal plane"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "IOCH"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Ionization chamber was used to measure energy",
                "loss of reaction products"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Plastic scintillation detectors were used to",
                "measure time of flight of projectile ions and reaction",
                "products. Two scintilation detectors were placed",
                "before the reaction target for incident particle",
                "identification"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The SeGA array of 32-fold segmented high-",
                "purity germanium detectors, was used to detect the",
                "de-excitation gamma rays emitted by the reaction",
                "residues. Sixteen of the SeGA detectors were arranged",
                "in two rings with relative angles of 90 deg (9",
                "detectors) and 37 deg (7 detectors) with respect to",
                "the beam axis. The high degree of segmentation allows",
                "for event-by-event Doppler reconstruction of the",
                "gamma rays emitted by the projectile-like reaction",
                "residues in flight."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "KINDT"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Projectile beam containing 48Cr and 50Fe was",
                "produced by fragmentation of a 160-MeV/nucleon 58Ni",
                "primary beam. The 893 mg/cm2 thick 9Be production",
                "target was located at the mid-acceptance target",
                "position of NSCL's A1900 fragment separator. An",
                "achromatic Al wedge of 300 mg/cm2 thickness together",
                "with slit systems were used to optimize the beam",
                "purity on 50Fe. The resulting cocktail beam of N = 24",
                "isotones was transmitted to the reaction target",
                "position of the S800 spectrograph at typical rates of",
                "2500, 2000, and 500 particles/s and purities of 39%,",
                "40%, and 11%, respectively, for 48Cr, 49Mn, and 50Fe",
                "at dp/p = 1% total A1900 momentum acceptance."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Reaction products were identified by energy loss and",
                "time of flight. Primary particles were identified by",
                "                    their time of flight."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "HISTORY": [
